  "answer": "In the poem *Resignation* (chapter 9 of *Old English Elegies*), the speaker opens with a direct prayer making the specific request: **\"Guide me, Almighty God, help me, Holy Lord!\"**[^1]\n\nThis sets the tone for the rest of the poem, which continues as an extended plea for divine guidance, mercy, protection from evil (especially at death), grace despite sins, and reception into eternal joy.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Unknown, *Old English Elegies*, ch. 9 (\"Resignation\"), [p-04f5b1](/works/unknown-old-english-elegies-d5fe9e/09-resignation/translation/#p-04f5b1).\n[^2]: Unknown, *Old English Elegies*, ch. 9 (\"Resignation\"), [full chapter](/works/unknown-old-english-elegies-d5fe9e/09-resignation/translation/).",
